          "id": 1,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"8356\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>A variable \\( x \\) is said to be live at a statement \\( s_{i} \\) in a program if the following three conditions hold simultaneously:</p>\n\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-roman\">\n\t<li>There exists a statement \\( S_{j} \\) that uses \\( x \\)</li>\n\t<li>There is a path from \\( S_{i} \\) to \\( S_{j} \\) in the flow graph corresponding to the program</li>\n\t<li>The path has no intervening assignment to \\( x \\) including at \\( S_{i} \\) and \\( S_{j} \\)\n\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"217\" src=\"images/gateOverflow_pyq_images/compiler_design___live_variable_analysis/8e69ed101a5ba7d0cb136809e6b63474.png\" width=\"402\"></p>\n\t</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>The variables which are live both at the statement in basic block \\( 2 \\) and at the statement in basic block \\( 3 \\) of the above control flow graph are</p>\n\n</div><br><br><b>GATE CSE 2015 Set 1 | Question: 50</b></p>",
          "type": "single",
          "options": [
            "<p>\\( \\text{p, s, u} \\)</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\text{r, s, u} \\)</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\text{r, u} \\)</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\text{q, v} \\)</p>"
          ],
          "correct_answer": "<p>\\( \\text{r, u} \\)</p>",
          "marks": 1,
          "negative_marks": 0.33,
          "explanation": "<p><a href=\"https://gateoverflow.in/8356/gate-cse-2015-set-1-question-50\" target=\"_blank\">https://gateoverflow.in/8356/gate-cse-2015-set-1-question-50</a></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"357502\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>For a statement \\( S \\) in a program, in the context of liveness analysis, the following sets are defined:</p>\n\n<p>\\( \\text{USE}(S) \\) : the set of variables used in \\( S \\)</p>\n\n<p>\\( \\text{IN}(S) \\) : the set of variables that are live at the entry of \\( S \\)</p>\n\n<p>\\( \\text{OUT}(S) \\) : the set of variables that are live at the exit of \\( S \\)</p>\n\n<p>Consider a basic block that consists of two statements, \\( S_1 \\) followed by \\( S_2 \\). Which one of the following statements is correct?</p>\n\n</div><br><br><b>GATE CSE 2021 Set 2 | Question: 38</b></p>",
          "type": "single",
          "options": [
            "<p>\\( \\text{OUT( \\)S_1\\( )}&nbsp;= \\text{IN ( \\)S_2\\( )} \\)</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\text{OUT ( \\)S_1\\( )}&nbsp;= \\text{IN ( \\)S_1\\( )} \\cup \\text{&nbsp;USE ( \\)S_1\\( )} \\)</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\text{OUT ( \\)S_1\\( )}&nbsp;= \\text{IN ( \\)S_2\\( ) }\\cup \\text{&nbsp;OUT ( \\)S_2\\( )} \\)</p>",
            "<p>\\( \\text{OUT ( \\)S_1\\( )}&nbsp;= \\text{USE ( \\)S_1\\( )} \\cup&nbsp;\\text{IN ( \\)S_2\\( )} \\)</p>"
          ],
          "correct_answer": "<p>\\( \\text{OUT( \\)S_1\\( )}&nbsp;= \\text{IN ( \\)S_2\\( )} \\)</p>",
          "marks": 1,
